This RP server sounds like a very cool idea. TLC is good in this, because it will force people to group to get the cool tradable(sp?) items instead of having a high level character harvest it and sell( e.g. lost temple of cazic thule with its ravenscale etc.). I mostly agree on the no PvP rules, but i would think that the extreme alignments should be able to battle eachother.Who on earth can imagine a pally and a SK walking near eachother without starting a fight? Likewise erudites and highelves would be inclined to fight those less civilized than they are, being all races but barbs, trolls and ogres in particular.<BR>To summarize i would be very much in favor of a system that lets people group based on alignment and common goals in a PvP environment where groups cannot kill players that are outside of the common goals of everyone in the group. I reallize that this is nearly impossible to do, so i think the current plans for this verver are just about the best they can be.<P>I will most certainly try this server( being a diehard RP-er as well as AD&D dm), and if i like it(very likely) it may even become my main playing server.<P>happily yours, <BR>jabblin level 40 slave of bristlebane on mith marr server
