<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
This is a brilliant idea!  The most wonderful thing about it is that there already seems to be an aversion from non-roleplayers to this rules set.  That pleases me immensely.  <BR>Trivial Loot Code.  Brilliant.  This will encourage team work, and inter level co operation.  People seeking ph4t l3wtz need not apply.<BR>Languages.  Genius.  This in itself will probably be so frustrating to |33t sp33k3rz that they will not play at all on this server.  Throw in the wonderful roleplaying angles, and lack of 'power leveling' languages and we have a hit.  I also like the learning curve. (At current it will require 100 hours per fluent language. That's an unbelievable rate in the real world.  Berlitz eat your heart out.)<BR>Bind.  Master stroke.  This is my FAVORITE, no exceptions.  This will promote a real fear of death amoung all characters.  The level of inconvenience is going to be a great motivator for 'realistic' levels of caution, especially when considering the horribly burdensome aftermath of a total party wipeout.  People are going to play like their lives depend on it.  White knuckle adrenilin moments are going to abound on this server.<BR>Alignment.  Fair enough. I would really like to see a span of alignments, not just good evil and neutral. I could offer some suggestions such as Benevolent, Honorable, Balanced, Selfish, Malevolent, Viscious, etc.  The descriptives alone would be nice to see.  More than three alignments could allow a greater range in experience penalties and bonuses.  Otherwise everyone is going to go neutral, out of necessity.<BR>PvE.  There is no other way. As for all of you who want PvP because it is more realistic...  You are playing the same EverQuest as me, right?  You are talking about realism with EQ's outlandish epic scale mechanics?  Every five to ten levels is an INSANE degree of difference in relative power levels and hit points.  The math is ludicrously UN-realistic.  By level 40, most characters are 100 times tougher than at level one.  PvP is for gamers, DUELS are for roleplayers.  <BR>Consider me there, day one on test.  *downloading test now*
</FONT>
