******************************************************************************************<P>I think its a great Idea and many of the elements sound nice. Here is what I think doesnt make. PVE ??? I think the customers want a server that might be realistic (hence roleplay) PVP would be more condusize to RP. What i think is needed here is a major EXP loss for killing someone of the oppsosite alignment. Or to make it better the person who attacked first. Oher things that would make it realistic would be no tells or guild speak, auctions or out of characters outside of designated areas (cities). This would probaly cause more people to group with whover was there rather than jsut thoier friends. It would also make an encounter with a friend a welcome surprise. Posted message boards (with mail options, you could mail someone a message) at various places would take the place of /who all friends and /shout LFG 30 mage.  I dont undertand how the TLC is a role playing aspect. i think it is possible to create a realistic  fanstay setting but you must make some sacrifces to balance. One thing should be considered.<P>The world is not balanced or fair. Why does EQ have to be. it actually takes away from the realness of it. Just an idea. maybe you wil come up with a serve full of necros and druids. if so make changes to the environment or even classes on that server only. i think this is a great chance to make EQ an even more immersive game. strive for how it would feel to not have telephones (/tell) and the yellow pages (/who all) as well as a perfect society (PVE) I have one last suggestion for PVP. Make it possible to get a badge of peace (that is visible is some way (name color change or somethin) in which when you are wearing it exp penalty for anyone attcking you would be as if they were the oppsoite alignment. Whilke wearing this badge you would always lose considerable exp for starting a fight. You could then have the person in the city who gave out the badge be a a certain faction to balance out  the abuse of this. If someone atacks people with badges then he cannot get one anymore. If someone kills with the badge on to many times then he cannot get the badges. I undertand there are may difent ways to make a PVP environment lets try some. One thing to note . notce how much btter PVE servers do. that is because of the fact that peole can abuse PVP. That is why creative solutions are necessary , i think everyone has though i wish i oculd just attack this guy, but he wont accept a duel. What we need is a set of rules and procedures that will allow PVP at anyitme but the penalty will be enourmous for abusing it. I think the no no drop idea is wonderful , I am sure it wil be abused by people with multi accounts but , so what. It also wil allow a high level character to give out stuff he found to friend and that will be a welocme chnage to the economie of some of these servers. any way i didnt giuve this much thought as it is early and Im at work. but the bottom line is :<BR>alot of people want a EQ server in which they really can become the character and immerse themselves in the world. My advice: D<P>Do not try to balance it and make it fair. Strive for realism and you will succeed!!.   <IMG SRC="eek.gif" border="0">   <IMG SRC="eek.gif" border="0">   <IMG SRC="redface.gif" border="0">   <IMG SRC="biggrin.gif" border="0">
